common error.  please read and understand the common error document.

I think the starts_with here won't cause mismatch, the starts_with here is used to match service with multiple instances, which service name is in serviceName@attribute format. In this case, serviceName@ is passed to this function. For services doesn't have multiple instances, the full serviceName is passed.

This is the existing implementation, I just moved to a new file for using this function across multiple files. Previously this function is at https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/49684/1/redfish-core/lib/network_protocol.hpp

That's fine, then split on the @ symbol and do an exact match on both sides of it.  As written, if you had a service named "dropbear_ssh_key" this code would fail.  We hit this failure a lot in practice, and it causes hard to debug issues, which is why we enforce this rule.
Got your point, I will fix it.
Done

How does this patchset relate to https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/49684?

They have merge conflicts on one another and they're editing the same code, both by the same author.  Based on how you pushed this, it's not clear what you intended here in terms of getting this merged

Aren't you assuming more of the path then you should?
Is it documented somewhere, these are all under control/service?

Services which can be configured by service-config-manager is under /xyz/openbmc_project/control/service. Documented at https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/tree/master/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Control/Service

> 
> I don't really think that's neccesary.  I like that we're calling systemd directly, and I'm not sure what calling service-config-manager would do for us.  Can you expand on why this would be better?

I don't see this question answered.

This is explained in the commit message of https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/51753/27, a patch prior to this one in this patchset.

In short, calling systemd dbus can only get the service status & port now, but it's hard to set as some settings like port need to write the service file. service-config-manager provides such API. But read from systemd, write by service-config-manager brings inconsistency as it takes time for the change to be applied. As service-config-manager author suggested, it's better to both read and write the same place.
Is this a typo? In https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/console.md there is a space between ~ and . (~ .), here space is missing (~.)

No, the space is not needed. The document need to be updated.

Standard SSH escape sequese is (You can check this by typing ~? in any SSH session)
 ~.   - terminate connection (and any multiplexed sessions)
 ~B   - send a BREAK to the remote system
 ~C   - open a command line
 ~R   - request rekey
 ~V/v - decrease/increase verbosity (LogLevel)
 ~^Z  - suspend ssh
 ~#   - list forwarded connections
 ~&   - background ssh (when waiting for connections to terminate)
 ~?   - this message
 ~~   - send the escape character by typing it twice
Ack
